There are 3 prisoners in a room. Two are wearing red hats, and one is wearing black hat. Each prisoner
can see all hat colors except his own. The prison guard tells them, “Each of you is wearing a red or a black
hat. Tell me your hat color, and you will be set free.” Since none of the prisoners can see their own hat,
nobody responds. Next the guard adds, “At least one person is wearing a red hat.” Soon afterwards, a
prisoner correctly identifies his hat color. How?


Notes:
Zielsetzung: Die eigene Hutfarbe wird entdeckt
Wenn das und das dann muss die eigene Hutfarbe das sein!
Wenn